{
  "texts": [
    "This median-based approach provides a robust estimate of the central frequency trajectory, mitigating the influence of local anomalies or measurement noise.",
    "As a system-level indicator, the interconnection RoCoF reflects the combined inertial response of the whole WECC footprint and serves as a baseline for evaluating regional and local deviations.",
    "Regional RoCoFAs detailed in Section III.C, we compute regional RoCoF over the first 0.5 sec following the disturbance.",
    "A higher regional RoCoF implies that the region is more susceptible to rapid frequency deviations, often due to high IBR penetration or insufficient local inertia.",
    "It serves as a key indicator of regional stability and helps differentiate regional response characteristics from the broader interconnection behavior."
  ]
}